claim.claim-text:
A method of registering a measured femur co-ordinate system to a model femur co-ordinate system, comprising;
(a) measuring in the measured co-ordinate system the location of a plurality of points (19) on a femur within a local distal femur region (18), each said point having a corresponding model point location within the model femur co-ordinate system; the method being characterised by
(b) fitting the measured points to the corresponding model points subject to the constraint of one or more correspondences between the measured and model co-ordinate systems, the one or more correspondences comprising a common remote point (7) in the measured and model coordinate system at a centre of the femoral head.
